Package it.polimi.ingsw.server.view

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BuilderBuiltObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed about the effective build if the result is true, the failure of a build attempt if the result is false
    BuilderMovementObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed about the effective movement of a builder, after a move or after a push event (the builder may have been moved by another player).
    BuilderPossibleBuildObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed about new possible destinations for a build, when it's the moment to build.
    BuilderPossibleMoveObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed about new possible destinations for a move, when it's the moment to move.
    BuildersPlacedObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed about the effective placement of a player builders if the result is true, the failure of a placement attempt if the result is false
    ChosenStepObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed about the result of a stepChoice, if result is true the step has been correctly chosen, otherwise the class is notified about a failure in step choice.
    ColorAssignmentObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed of the actual assignment of builders color for a player, if the result is false the class is notified about a wrong attempt of color choice.
    EndGameObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed of the end of the game and the winner.
    ErrorsObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed of generic errors of wrong insertion or wrong number of players insertion
    GodChoiceObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed of the actual assignment if a player godCard or match godCards.
    PlayerAddedObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed of the actual insertion of a new player.
    PlayerLoseObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed whether a player loses but the match continues (when no one has won yet).
    PlayerTurnObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed of a turn change.
    StartPlayerSetObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed of the actual choice of the start player.
    StateObserver
    This interface is implemented to be informed of a Model state change.
    ViewSelectObserver
    Interface implemented to be informed of a new current Client, identified by his nickname.
